<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><channel><title>Thailand on Mountain Diaries</title><link>https://mountaindiaries.com/countries/thailand/</link><description>Recent content in Thailand on Mountain Diaries</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 03 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://mountaindiaries.com/countries/thailand/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Climbing in Thailand &amp;amp; Laos</title><link>https://mountaindiaries.com/posts/climbing-in-thailand-laos/</link><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">https://mountaindiaries.com/posts/climbing-in-thailand-laos/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Two weeks of rock climbing in &lt;a href="https://basecamptonsai.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;Tonsai&lt;/a&gt;/Railey Beach and Ao Nang in Krabi, Southern Thailand and a month in &lt;a href="https://www.greenclimbershome.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;Green Climbers Home&lt;/a&gt; in Laos as a beginner in rock climbing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When: Nov/Dec 2023&lt;br&gt;
Where: Krabi (Tonsai/Railey Beach, Ao Nang) and Green Climbers Home (Thakhek, Laos)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class="mx-auto my-0 rounded-md"&gt;
&lt;img src="https://mountaindiaries.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/cleanshot-2024-01-02-at-14.29.22402x.png" alt="climbing-thailand-laos-1" class="mx-auto my-0 rounded-md"/&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href="https://mountaindiaries.com/posts/climbing-in-thailand-laos/#krabi"&gt;Krabi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href="https://mountaindiaries.com/posts/climbing-in-thailand-laos/#green-climbers-home-laos"&gt;Green Climbers Home, Laos&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="krabi" class="relative group"&gt;Krabi &lt;span class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100"&gt;&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700" style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#krabi" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;figure class="mx-auto my-0 rounded-md"&gt;
&lt;img src="https://mountaindiaries.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_6993.jpg" alt="climbing-thailand-laos-2" class="mx-auto my-0 rounded-md"/&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From Bangkok, it&amp;rsquo;s an hour flight to Krabi Airport. From the airport, take a shuttle bus to Ao Nang (40 mins). From Ao Nang, it&amp;rsquo;s 20 mins boat ride to either Tonsai or Railey Beach. If you&amp;rsquo;re getting on the boat during high tide, you will most likely have to walk at least knee deep in water so I recommend sandles + shorts.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>